}

import os
import fileinput

# Ensure we are in a stable directory before proceeding
%cd /content

# Get GitHub credentials for cloning

GITHUB_REPO = os.environ.get("GITHUB_REPO")
GITHUB_TOKEN = os.environ.get("GITHUB_TOKEN") # Assuming it's set as environment variable or Colab secret

if not GITHUB_USER or not GITHUB_REPO or not GITHUB_TOKEN:

REMOTE_URL = f"https://{GITHUB_TOKEN}:x-oauth-basic@github.com/{GITHUB_USER}/{GITHUB_REPO}.git"

# Ensure the target directory is clean before cloning

# Clone the user's fork directly
!git clone {REMOTE_URL} /content/ouroboros_repo
%cd /content/ouroboros_repo

        else:
            print(line, end='')

# Install dependencies
